<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1348,1663]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,1348,1374]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[312,376,1349,1375]" name="Japan" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Honshu, Kyushu, Shikoku) (
<bibRefCitation author="Dettmer, H. S. J." box="[716,934,1348,1374]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="123 - 132" refId="ref43442" refString="Dettmer, H. S. J. (1934) Vier neue Neuroterus - Arten aus Japan. Broteria, 3, 123 - 132." type="journal article" year="1934">Dettmer 1934: 128</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakagami, S." box="[947,1169,1348,1375]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="67 - 79" refId="ref52473" refString="Sakagami, S. (1952) Zur Cynipoidenfauna Japan und seiner Nachbarlander (Hymenoptera). Mushi, 24, 67 - 79." type="journal article" year="1952">Sakagami 1952: 72</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[1181,1384,1348,1375]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="15 - 21" refId="ref48520" refString="Monzen, K. (1953) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (I). Cynipidae (Cynipinae), Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of the Gakugei Faculty of the Iwate University, 5, 15 - 21." type="journal article" year="1953">Monzen 1953: 16</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda 1996: 136</bibRefCitation>
, 141).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1348,1663]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1420,1446]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
The alternating lifecycle was closed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[774,1074,1420,1446]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and the asexual generation was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[300,502,1456,1482]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="812 - 830" refId="ref44445" refString="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y. (2016) First description of asexual generation and taxonomic revision of the gall wasp genus Latuspina (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 109 (5), 812 - 830. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / saw 051" type="journal article" year="2016">Ide &amp; Abe (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1348,1663]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,310,1492,1518]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks (2).</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[318,623,1492,1518]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
photographed the sexual gall and described it as ‘Kunugi-haname-kotogari-tama-fushi’ (C-095), and the asexual gall as ‘Kunugi-ha-suji-kotsuno-tama-fushi’ (C-083). Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="812 - 830" refId="ref44445" refString="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y. (2016) First description of asexual generation and taxonomic revision of the gall wasp genus Latuspina (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 109 (5), 812 - 830. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / saw 051" type="journal article" year="2016">Ide &amp; Abe (2016)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that these galls correspond to the sexual and asexual generations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ide &amp; Abe" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Dettmer" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[1116,1241,1564,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Latuspina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hellwegi">
<emphasis box="[1116,1241,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">L. hellwegi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1348,1663]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1600,1626]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Biology.</emphasis>
The catkin galls of the sexual generation and the detachable leaf galls of the asexual generation both develop on 
<taxonomicName box="[282,436,1636,1662]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutissima">
<emphasis box="[282,436,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Q. acutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[490,631,1636,1662]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[490,631,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Q. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[706,778,1636,1662]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cerris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[706,778,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cerris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[900,1085,1636,1662]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="812 - 830" refId="ref44445" refString="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y. (2016) First description of asexual generation and taxonomic revision of the gall wasp genus Latuspina (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 109 (5), 812 - 830. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / saw 051" type="journal article" year="2016">Ide &amp; Abe 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
